frameDefinitions: An Agent or a Cause causes a Fluid to move from a Source to a Goal along a Path or within an Area.
An Agent acts according to a <em>
An Excreter excretes Excreta. 'Principal Skinner burped on me.'
In this frame a Source_emitter discharges its Emission along a Path or to a Goal.  ' (1)
In this frame a Patient is in a phase brought about after a change of phase.
In this frame a Fluid moves from a Source to a Goal along a Path or within an Area.  '
frameExamples: Health authorities say they have put measures into <t>effect</t> in all ports of entry and in centers of provinces.
(1) The factory <t>exudes</t> toxic fumes from three large chimneys.
Collect up the  <t>thawed</t> water from the freezer section.
listRoleDefinitions: The animate protagonist who causes the <fen>Fluid</fen> to move.
An event or force that causes the <fen>Fluid</fen> to move.
The entity that changes location and moves in a fluidic way. It is not necessarily in a liquid state but is construed that way.
The location that the <fen>Fluid</fen> occupies initially.
<fen>Goal</fen> is the location the <fen>Fluid</fen> ends up in as a result  of the motion
The trajectory along which the Fluid moves, exclusive of the <fen>Source</fen> and <fen>Goal</fen>.
The setting in which the <fen>Fluid</fen>'s movement takes place along an unspecified <fen>Path</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the fluidic motion event is caused.
The location where the motion takes place.
The <fen>Plan</fen> is a goal or purpose that the <fen>Agent</fen> carries out.

The <fen>Agent</fen>, often an institution or governmental organization, puts a <fen>Plan</fen> into effect. The Agent is generally a primary participant in the <fen>Plan</fen>, but a separate <fen>Focal_participant</fen> may be specified.
This role describes the medium through which a plan was executed.  It may occur in the same syntactic position as the Agent.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the Agent puts the <fen>Plan</fen> into effect.

The <fen>Place</fen> at which the <fen>Plan</fen> is or is not operational.

[CHANGE: or, place where agent puts into effect? 2 fes?]
The <fen>Excreta</fen> is the waste expelled by the body.
The <fen>Excreter</fen> is the agent who excretes the <fen>Excreta</fen>.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the starting point of the <fen>Excreta</fen>'s motion.
When the <fen>Excreter</fen> engages in excretion.
This role identifieis the <fen>Place</fen> where the excretion occurs.
The <fen>Source_emitter</fen> is the item  from which the <fen>Emission</fen> are discharged.
The <fen>Emission</fen>s are discharged out of the <fen>Source_emitter</fen> .
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when  the <fen>Source_emitter</fen> emits the <fen>Emission</fen>.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is the entity which has had its phase altered.
<fen>Area</fen> is the setting in which the <fen>Fluid</fen>'s movement takes place on an unspecified <fen>Path</fen>.
<fen>Goal</fen> is the location the <fen>Fluid</fen> ends up.
The <fen>Path</fen> is the trajectory along which the <fen>Fluid</fen> moves.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the location the <fen>Fluid</fen> occupies initially.
The <fen>Fluid</fen> is the entity that changes location and moves in a fluidic way.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Fluid</fen> flows.
The Place describes the location of the motion which has a specified Source, Path or Goal.
listRoleExamples: What happens if <fex>we</fex> drip acid on this compound?
Why did  you squirt juice <fex>onto my chair</fex>?
I spattered the egg all over the floor <fex>in the kitchen</fex>.
The policy will be implemented <fex>by a new computer system</fex>.
Dr. Nick vomited <fex>puke</fex> across the table.
<fex>At Oregon Caves</fex>, a stream runs through the dining room.
